From COCHRANE JAMES SHAPLEIGH Subject Re Riddle me In article Dan Hartung writes COCHRANE JAMES SHAPLEIGH writes On the subject of CS CN tear gas when I received my initial introduction to You couldn't find a window after six hours Daniel Hartung Ask me about Rotaract Have you ever been violently sick repeatedly I have and it was difficult to drag myself back to my bed much less move through a building full of smoke and debris especially when most likely already disoriented from lack of sleep and constant psychological Throw in the fact that the 'safety' outside consists of people who have shot at me and thrown grenades at me and are currently knocking my house down with tanks I could understand if the BD's were inclined to stay put in the center of the James Cochrane When in danger or in doubt run in This space circles scream and for rent